{
  "video_id": "R3tbVHlsKhs",
  "title": "Does time exist? - Andrew Zimmerman Jones",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 20400.0,
      "end_time": 22619.0,
      "text": "The earliest time measurements were"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 22620.0,
      "end_time": 25330.0,
      "text": "observations of cycles of the natural world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 25330.0,
      "end_time": 28259.0,
      "text": "using patterns of changes from day to night"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 28260.0,
      "end_time": 31800.0,
      "text": "and season to season to build calendars."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 31800.0,
      "end_time": 34840.0,
      "text": "More precise time-keeping, like sundials"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 34840.0,
      "end_time": 37600.0,
      "text": "and mechanical clocks, eventually came along"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 37600.0,
      "end_time": 40720.0,
      "text": "to put time in more convenient boxes."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 40720.0,
      "end_time": 43485.0,
      "text": "But what exactly is it that we’re measuring?"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 43485.0,
      "end_time": 45765.0,
      "text": "Is time something that physically exists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 45765.0,
      "end_time": 47995.0,
      "text": "or is it just in our heads?"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 48600.0,
      "end_time": 50296.0,
      "text": "At first the answer seems obvious—"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 50296.0,
      "end_time": 51966.0,
      "text": "of course time exists;"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 51966.0,
      "end_time": 54246.0,
      "text": "it constantly unfolds all around us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 54246.0,
      "end_time": 57536.0,
      "text": "and it’s hard to imagine the universe without it."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 57536.0,
      "end_time": 59956.0,
      "text": "But our understanding of time started"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 59956.0,
      "end_time": 63226.0,
      "text": "getting complicated thanks to Einstein."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 63226.0,
      "end_time": 65646.0,
      "text": "His theory of relativity tells us that time"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 65646.0,
      "end_time": 68526.0,
      "text": "passes for everyone, but doesn’t always pass"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 68526.0,
      "end_time": 71916.0,
      "text": "at the same rate for people in different situations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 71916.0,
      "end_time": 74566.0,
      "text": "like those travelling close to the speed of light"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 74566.0,
      "end_time": 78600.0,
      "text": "or orbiting a supermassive black hole."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 78600.0,
      "end_time": 81196.0,
      "text": "Einstein resolved the malleability of time"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 81196.0,
      "end_time": 84816.0,
      "text": "by combining it with space to define space-time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 84816.0,
      "end_time": 89856.0,
      "text": "which can bend, but behaves in consistent, predictable ways"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 89856.0,
      "end_time": 92386.0,
      "text": "Einstein’s theory seemed to confirm that time"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 92386.0,
      "end_time": 95606.0,
      "text": "is woven into the very fabric of the universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 95606.0,
      "end_time": 99360.0,
      "text": "But there’s a big question it didn’t fully resolve:"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 99360.0,
      "end_time": 102536.0,
      "text": "why is it we can move through space in any direction,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 102536.0,
      "end_time": 104866.0,
      "text": "but through time in only one?"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 104866.0,
      "end_time": 108460.0,
      "text": "No matter what we do, the past is always,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 108460.0,
      "end_time": 110586.0,
      "text": "stubbornly, behind us."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 110586.0,
      "end_time": 113706.0,
      "text": "This is called the arrow of time."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 113706.0,
      "end_time": 115926.0,
      "text": "When a drop of food coloring is"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 115926.0,
      "end_time": 117606.0,
      "text": "dropped into a glass of water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 117606.0,
      "end_time": 120306.0,
      "text": "we instinctively know that the coloring"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 120306.0,
      "end_time": 122206.0,
      "text": "will drift out from the drop,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 122206.0,
      "end_time": 124366.0,
      "text": "eventually filling the glass."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 124366.0,
      "end_time": 126906.0,
      "text": "Imagine watching the opposite happen."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 126906.0,
      "end_time": 131346.0,
      "text": "Here, we’d recognize time as unfolding backwards."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 131346.0,
      "end_time": 133996.0,
      "text": "We live in a universe where the food coloring"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 133996.0,
      "end_time": 135556.0,
      "text": "spreads out in the water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 135556.0,
      "end_time": 138106.0,
      "text": "not a universe where it collects together."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 138106.0,
      "end_time": 140856.0,
      "text": "In physics, this is described by"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 140856.0,
      "end_time": 143126.0,
      "text": "the Second Law of Thermodynamics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 143126.0,
      "end_time": 146116.0,
      "text": "which says that systems will gain disorder,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 146116.0,
      "end_time": 148786.0,
      "text": "or entropy, over time."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 148786.0,
      "end_time": 152506.0,
      "text": "Systems in our universe move from order to disorder,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 152506.0,
      "end_time": 154456.0,
      "text": "and it is that property of the universe"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 154456.0,
      "end_time": 158416.0,
      "text": "that defines the direction of time’s arrow."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 158416.0,
      "end_time": 161446.0,
      "text": "So if time is such a fundamental property,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 161446.0,
      "end_time": 164116.0,
      "text": "it should be in our most fundamental equations"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 164116.0,
      "end_time": 166686.0,
      "text": "describing the universe, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 166686.0,
      "end_time": 168260.0,
      "text": "We currently have two sets of"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 168260.0,
      "end_time": 169916.0,
      "text": "equations that govern physics."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 169916.0,
      "end_time": 172121.0,
      "text": "General relativity describes the"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 172121.0,
      "end_time": 174311.0,
      "text": "behavior of very large things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 174311.0,
      "end_time": 178251.0,
      "text": "while quantum physics explains the very small."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 178251.0,
      "end_time": 180871.0,
      "text": "One of the biggest goals in theoretical physics"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 180871.0,
      "end_time": 183941.0,
      "text": "over the last half century has been reconciling"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 183941.0,
      "end_time": 188771.0,
      "text": "the two into one fundamental “theory of everything.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 188771.0,
      "end_time": 190400.0,
      "text": "There have been many attempts"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 190401.0,
      "end_time": 192101.0,
      "text": "—none yet proven—"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 192101.0,
      "end_time": 194351.0,
      "text": "and they treat time in different ways."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 194351.0,
      "end_time": 198910.0,
      "text": "Oddly enough, one contender called the Wheeler-DeWitt"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 198910.0,
      "end_time": 201661.0,
      "text": "equation, doesn’t include time at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 201661.0,
      "end_time": 203991.0,
      "text": "Like all current theories of everything,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 203991.0,
      "end_time": 206131.0,
      "text": "that equation is speculative."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 206131.0,
      "end_time": 207841.0,
      "text": "But as a thought experiment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 207841.0,
      "end_time": 211171.0,
      "text": "if it or a similarly time-starved equation"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 211171.0,
      "end_time": 213541.0,
      "text": "turned out to be true, would that mean"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 213541.0,
      "end_time": 217910.0,
      "text": "that time doesn’t exist, at the most fundamental level?"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 217910.0,
      "end_time": 220681.0,
      "text": "Could time just be some sort of illusion generated"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 220681.0,
      "end_time": 222351.0,
      "text": "by the limitations of the way"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 222351.0,
      "end_time": 224910.0,
      "text": "we perceive the universe?"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 224910.0,
      "end_time": 226191.0,
      "text": "We don’t yet know, but maybe that’s"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 226191.0,
      "end_time": 227981.0,
      "text": "the wrong way of thinking about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 227981.0,
      "end_time": 232191.0,
      "text": "Instead of asking if time exists as a fundamental property,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 232191.0,
      "end_time": 235711.0,
      "text": "maybe it could exist as an emergent one."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 235711.0,
      "end_time": 239711.0,
      "text": "Emergent properties are things that don’t exist"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 239711.0,
      "end_time": 241871.0,
      "text": "in individual pieces of a system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 241871.0,
      "end_time": 244751.0,
      "text": "but do exist for the system as a whole."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 244751.0,
      "end_time": 248471.0,
      "text": "Each individual water molecule doesn’t have a tide,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 248471.0,
      "end_time": 250941.0,
      "text": "but the whole ocean does."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 250941.0,
      "end_time": 253821.0,
      "text": "A movie creates change through time by using"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 253821.0,
      "end_time": 257461.0,
      "text": "a series of still images that appear to have a fluid,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 257461.0,
      "end_time": 259761.0,
      "text": "continuous change between them."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 259761.00000000003,
      "end_time": 261741.00000000003,
      "text": "Flipping through the images fast enough,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 261741.0,
      "end_time": 264461.0,
      "text": "our brains perceive the passage of time"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 264461.0,
      "end_time": 266801.0,
      "text": "from the sequence of still images."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 266801.0,
      "end_time": 269700.0,
      "text": "No individual frame of the movie changes"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 269701.0,
      "end_time": 272181.0,
      "text": "or contains the passage of time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 272181.0,
      "end_time": 274481.0,
      "text": "but it’s a property that comes out of how"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 274481.0,
      "end_time": 277591.0,
      "text": "the pieces are strung together."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 277591.0,
      "end_time": 281410.0,
      "text": "The movement is real, yet also an illusion."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 281410.0,
      "end_time": 285641.0,
      "text": "Could the physics of time somehow be a similar illusion?"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 285641.0,
      "end_time": 289461.0,
      "text": "Physicists are still exploring these and other questions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 289461.0,
      "end_time": 292101.0,
      "text": "so we’re far from a complete explanation."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 292101.0,
      "end_time": 294411.0,
      "text": "At least for the moment."
    }
  ]
}